Route 1. Not recommended!
Very steep and requires hands on to reach the summit. My route 2 is longer but an easier ascent. I would not descend this route.
Easier than the direct route from the CP. Contours around the hill more.
Plenty of parking in the caving club car park at SN 855 155
Link route between the two summits

track_title: Fan Gyhirych and Fan Nedd Linear from Penwyllt. Feb 2020.

track_notes: Car parking at layby. Stile on fence provides entry to the hillside. Route is moderately difficult across boggy ground and steepish incline, no visible path to follow. Access the summit via the northern almost-chimney/stream. Route to Fan Nedd far better on dirt road. I do not recommend following my return, which followed a fenceline to the forest, had to cross a large stretch of bog to return. Suggest routing back down north chimney if conditions allow.
track_title: Fan Gyhirych and Fan Nedd via bog beside A4067.

track_notes: Enough room to park 5 cars at start, quite boggy in places through-out winter months, but a lovely hike in the summer time.
